flow.mentorSays:
Let's understand what this Shopping Cart challenge asks for.

**Challenge Description:**
const products = [
  { id: 1, name: "Laptop", price: 999 },
  { id: 2, name: "Mouse", price: 29 },
  { id: 3, name: "Keyboard", price: 79 }
];

// Requirements:
// - Product list with "Add to Cart" buttons
// - Cart sidebar/section showing:
//   - Items with quantities
//   - Increase/decrease quantity buttons
//   - Remove item button
//   - Subtotal per item
//   - Total price
// - Update total automatically
// - Disable "Add to Cart" if already in cart
// - Show cart count badge

**What we need to build:**
This challenge tests your understanding of Complex state, calculations.

**Time estimate:** 30 minutes
**Difficulty level:** Senior

This is a practical interview question that tests your understanding of core Angular concepts and your ability to implement them correctly.

